  ('HDL cholesterol has an inverse relationship with cardiovascular risk. HDL < 1.0 mmol/L in men and < 1.2 mmol/L in women is a risk factor in the 2023 Australian CVD Risk Guideline. LDL drives atherosclerotic plaque formation through oxidised LDL incorporation into macrophage foam cells. Each 1 mmol/L reduction in LDL is associated with approximately 22% reduction in major cardiovascular events.', '[0,-0.4609375,-0.265625,-0.375,0,-0.0234375,0.234375,0.84375,0.0390625,-0.984375,0.0234375,0.0234375,-0.078125,-0.4375,0.171875,-0.140625,0.3515625,-0.4140625,-0.1796875,-0.03125,-0.03125,-0.1640625,-0.4296875,-0.3671875,-0.9453125,0.3671875,-0.046875,-0.015625,-0.1171875,0.3828125,-0.34375,-0.0703125,0.78125,-0.1640625,0.015625,0.0859375,-0.28125,-0.1875,-0.671875,0.34375,0.3359375,0.2265625,-0.1796875,-0.03125,-0.078125,0.0234375,-0.0546875,-0.1171875,-0.0546875,-0.1328125,-0.1484375,-0.28125,0.625,0.203125,0.1953125,-0.546875,0.6953125,0.0234375,0.296875,-0.5078125,-0.3359375,0.3671875,-0.203125,0.5,-0.0390625,0.359375,-0.2890625,0.0390625,-0.2109375,0.2109375,-0.484375,-0.2421875,-0.6640625,0.3828125,0.1015625,0.53125,-0.109375,0.2578125,-0.4609375,0.09375,0.0625,-0.3828125,0.0625,0.8203125,0.0390625,0.5,0.515625,0.359375,-0.4140625,-0.6953125,0.0703125,0.3125,0.046875,0.03125,-0.1796875,0,0.1875,-0.375,0.6796875,-0.109375,-0.234375,-0.015625,-0.15625,-0.4375,0.453125,-0.6640625,-0.1484375,-0.03125,0.1875,0.1484375,-0.375,-0.1796875,-0.4453125,0.3046875,0.296875,0.34375,0.21875,-0.234375,0.0078125,-0.0703125,-0.203125,0.265625,-0.3203125,0.140625,0.109375,0.171875,0.40625,0.6171875,0.15625,-0.359375,-0.734375,-0.2734375,0.140625,0.0234375,-0.296875,0.0625,-0.3828125,-0.234375,-0.0546875,-0.0546875,0.3125,-0.109375,0.1328125,-0.15625,-0.03125,0.0703125,0.1953125,-0.1171875,0.25,0,0.2578125,0.2734375,-0.078125,0.40625,0.2109375,0.4453125,0.2265625,0.234375,-0.03125,-0.015625,-0.09375,-0.125,-0.7265625,-0.265625,0.296875,0.046875,-0.265625,0.0390625,0.03125,-0.25,0.101