  ('Atrial fibrillation (AF) independently increases stroke risk 5-fold. The CHA2DS2-VASc score is used to determine anticoagulation therapy: score ≥ 2 in males or ≥ 3 in females warrants anticoagulation. Undetected AF affects ~1–2% of Australians. Pulse palpation and ECG screening for AF is recommended in all adults > 65 years. Source: National Heart Foundation of Australia 2018.', '[0,-0.2734375,-0.078125,0.0625,0,-0.0390625,-0.0703125,0.625,0.0234375,-0.9921875,0.375,0.3515625,0.0390625,-0.375,-0.2109375,0.015625,0.3828125,0.109375,-0.09375,-0.015625,-0.1953125,0.0546875,-0.640625,-0.65625,-0.5390625,0,-0.1953125,0.375,0.1171875,0.0859375,-0.4140625,0.0390625,0.2109375,0.1328125,-0.2734375,0.1953125,-0.046875,0.1328125,-0.265625,0.2265625,0.265625,0.15625,0.0390625,0.0390625,-0.4453125,0.03125,0.40625,-0.3984375,-0.140625,-0.5078125,0.03125,0.1328125,-0.2265625,0.1796875,-0.265625,-0.4375,0.0234375,-0.1484375,0.6171875,-0.515625,0.015625,-0.2109375,0.0703125,0.1484375,-0.0234375,0.375,-0.40625,-0.4765625,0.0390625,0.6328125,-0.15625,-0.046875,0.171875,0.2734375,0.046875,0.328125,-0.1484375,0.1640625,-0.7265625,0.25,-0.3984375,-0.5234375,0.4375,0.8515625,0.2734375,0.21875,0.4140625,0.1328125,0.1015625,-0.1953125,-0.234375,0.078125,-0.265625,-0.359375,-0.046875,-0.0390625,0.171875,-0.6015625,0.234375,-0.1796875,-0.53125,-0.4453125,0.0859375,-0.2421875,0.46875,-0.2265625,0.0625,-0.140625,-0.078125,-0.0390625,-0.3203125,-0.40625,-0.390625,-0.1171875,0.4765625,0,0.1328125,-0.578125,0.03125,-0.296875,-0.0625,-0.375,-0.59375,0.078125,-0.4140625,0.0390625,0.2890625,0.390625,-0.234375,0.2734375,-0.796875,-0.0390625,0.1171875,-0.1640625,-0.2109375,-0.1171875,-0.1875,0.046875,-0.421875,-0.171875,0.1875,-0.203125,-0.1953125,0.2578125,-0.1796875,-0.3046875,0.328125,-0.3203125,-0.15625,0.15625,0.0234375,-0.1796875,-0.21875,-0.1953125,0.125,0.140625,0.3828125,0.328125,0.0703125,0.0078125,-0.0703125,0.125,-0.3828125,-0.6171875,0.15625,-0.015625,-0.46875,0.1171875,0.0625,0.546875