  ('Sleep deprivation (< 6 hours/night) is independently associated with impaired glucose metabolism. Short sleep increases cortisol and ghrelin, decreases leptin, and promotes insulin resistance. Studies show a 28% higher risk of T2DM in individuals sleeping < 6 hours vs 7–8 hours. Sleep optimisation is a modifiable metabolic intervention. Source: Cappuccio et al., Diabetes Care 2010.', '[0,0.0546875,0.1171875,-0.5078125,0,0.1640625,0.09375,0.7109375,0.0859375,-0.984375,0.3125,0.03125,0.21875,-0.1171875,0.8203125,-0.265625,-0.40625,-0.375,0.359375,0.015625,0.03125,0.03125,-0.4375,-0.90625,-0.515625,-0.2734375,-0.015625,0.5625,0.3359375,0.421875,-0.3046875,0.2265625,0.5625,0.28125,-0.03125,-0.53125,0.4375,0.0546875,-0.34375,0.6640625,-0.15625,0.4921875,-0.4140625,0.3359375,0.484375,-0.2265625,0.234375,0.09375,0.203125,0.09375,-0.171875,-0.2421875,0.0625,0.296875,0.3984375,0.1875,0.4296875,0.0546875,-0.4921875,-0.3828125,0.09375,-0.0234375,-0.046875,0.53125,0.2421875,-0.015625,0.3359375,0.046875,-0.203125,-0.5546875,-0.3203125,0.0078125,0.0234375,0.375,0.515625,0.390625,-0.3671875,-0.5625,0.0703125,0.171875,-0.015625,0.2265625,0.15625,0.8515625,-0.21875,0.3125,0.234375,0.2421875,-0.34375,0.1328125,-0.2890625,-0.0546875,-0.1171875,-0.234375,0.2421875,0.2421875,0.125,0.125,0.0078125,-0.0390625,-0.140625,-0.1484375,-0.140625,0.234375,0.5546875,0.1015625,0.171875,-0.0234375,0.328125,0.328125,-0.1796875,0.2265625,0.5703125,0.1875,0.7578125,0.3828125,0.7109375,-0.4765625,-0.25,-0.34375,0.4609375,0.34375,0.4609375,-0.0390625,-0.09375,-0.3359375,-0.078125,0.1484375,-0.359375,0.203125,-0.78125,-0.1484375,0.3203125,-0.234375,0.3125,-0.0703125,0.0078125,0.0546875,-0.375,0.40625,0.1484375,-0.015625,-0.0234375,-0.5703125,-0.1328125,0.1953125,-0.15625,0.0234375,-0.1875,-0.1796875,-0.2109375,0.2265625,0.09375,-0.1171875,0.15625,-0.2421875,-0.046875,0.5625,0.1640625,0.015625,-0.3671875,0.078125,-0.2734375,-0.421875,0.34375,0.3515625,-0.21875,0.109375,0.4921875,0.1640625,0.0078125,0.