  ('Elevated serum uric acid (hyperuricaemia: > 420 µmol/L male / > 360 µmol/L female) is associated with gout, chronic kidney disease, and metabolic syndrome. Uric acid inhibits insulin signalling and is an independent predictor of T2DM onset. Fructose consumption (high-fructose corn syrup, soft drinks) is the primary dietary driver of elevated uric acid. Reducing fructose intake lowers uric acid by 10–15%.', '[0,0.40625,-0.0546875,-0.6953125,0,-0.3515625,0.3046875,0.7421875,0.125,-0.984375,0.2265625,0.234375,-0.0703125,-0.1484375,0.7578125,0.15625,-0.4296875,-0.5390625,0.3671875,0.0078125,-0.2578125,0.078125,-0.7890625,-0.5234375,-0.9296875,0.328125,-0.21875,0.2109375,0.0625,0.6796875,-0.1640625,0.2421875,0.8046875,-0.4921875,-0.03125,-0.3515625,-0.28125,0.046875,-0.1015625,0.3125,-0.1875,0.6171875,0.359375,0.34375,-0.2109375,-0.46875,0.2734375,-0.03125,-0.0625,-0.140625,0.171875,-0.0625,0.0078125,0.0234375,0.328125,-0.2734375,0.09375,-0.0078125,-0.15625,-0.03125,0.234375,0.0703125,-0.0859375,0.234375,-0.3125,-0.25,-0.1484375,-0.0859375,0.234375,0.0703125,-0.5390625,0.5546875,0.03125,0.0390625,0.0625,0.5390625,0.0390625,-0.421875,-0.484375,0.6171875,-0.3828125,0.046875,0.53125,0.9296875,0.15625,-0.1171875,0.1015625,-0.375,-0.046875,0.015625,-0.09375,0.40625,0.1796875,-0.15625,0.296875,0.6328125,0.0390625,-0.0390625,0.0546875,-0.25,-0.453125,-0.4375,-0.1796875,0.1328125,0.546875,0.4375,-0.046875,0.34375,0.234375,-0.09375,-0.015625,0.578125,0.1796875,0.25,0.21875,-0.65625,0.46875,0.0390625,0.0078125,-0.6171875,0.125,-0.1328125,0.578125,-0.234375,-0.53125,0.3828125,-0.3515625,0.1328125,-0.3671875,0.359375,-0.75,0.1875,-0.09375,-0.3125,-0.28125,0,-0.1015625,-0.0234375,-0.3203125,-0.203125,0.1484375,-0.2578125,-0.09375,-0.109375,-0.2890625,0.2421875,0.1796875,0.1484375,0.1484375,-0.03125,-0.0703125,0.1171875,0.359375,0.40625,0.015625,-0.5546875,-0.0859375,0.1171875,-0.140625,0.078125,0.546875,-0.1171875,-0.6875,-0.15625,0.0390625,-0.4375,0.109375,0.0546875,-0.0546875,-