  ('Hearing loss is the largest single modifiable dementia risk factor in midlife, accounting for 8.2% of population attributable risk (PAR) in the 2024 Lancet Commission. Untreated hearing loss is associated with social withdrawal, reduced cognitive stimulation, and accelerated cognitive decline. Hearing aid use in people with moderate hearing loss reduces the rate of cognitive decline by approximately 50% (ACHIEVE trial, Lancet 2023).', '[0,0.3046875,-0.546875,0.203125,0,0.234375,0.484375,0.1171875,0.109375,-0.6953125,0.0234375,0.4921875,0.1328125,-0.25,-0.0625,-0.21875,-0.21875,0.15625,-0.2421875,-0.015625,0.0703125,-0.046875,-0.2265625,-0.0625,-0.3359375,0.046875,0.0234375,-0.1015625,0.375,0.2109375,-0.5078125,0.15625,-0.0078125,0.6015625,0.0703125,0.21875,0.0390625,-0.015625,-0.4296875,0.515625,-0.203125,0.5234375,0.140625,0.1484375,-0.3203125,-0.4765625,0.34375,-0.3359375,0.2421875,0.09375,-0.078125,0.1484375,0.140625,0.1953125,0.1015625,-0.0234375,0.421875,-0.1796875,-0.0078125,-0.359375,-0.0078125,-0.15625,0.0546875,0.234375,0.203125,0.2578125,0.0234375,-0.703125,0.2109375,-0.0546875,-0.546875,0.0390625,0.46875,0.3203125,0.3671875,-0.21875,0.171875,0.1328125,-0.3046875,-0.1171875,-0.6953125,-0.296875,0.125,0.6875,0.171875,-0.4609375,-0.15625,-0.046875,-0.34375,-0.3046875,-0.03125,0.2578125,0.2734375,-0.3984375,-0.0078125,0.296875,0.328125,-0.375,0.4375,-0.046875,0.3828125,-0.1015625,0.1953125,-0.09375,0.4609375,0.3125,-0.1953125,0.3828125,-0.0390625,0.1953125,-0.1875,-0.078125,-0.3046875,0.4140625,0.609375,0.296875,0.34375,-0.0625,0.0859375,-0.453125,-0.375,0.40625,-0.21875,0.078125,-0.109375,-0.4453125,0.0234375,0.2265625,-0.2109375,0.28125,-0.6953125,-0.046875,0.6953125,-0.28125,0.234375,0.1953125,-0.2109375,0.1015625,0.1953125,-0.09375,-0.1875,0.0390625,-0.109375,0.1171875,-0.34375,-0.34375,0.21875,-0.1796875,-0.046875,-0.1796875,0.0078125,-0.1171875,-0.28125,0.1171875,-0.0625,0.15625,0.046875,0.1171875,0.0546875,0,-0.046875,-0.1953125,-0.3984375,-0.67968