  ('Depression is both a risk factor and an early symptom of dementia — the causal relationship is bidirectional. Depression in midlife increases dementia risk by approximately 65%. Mechanisms include HPA axis dysregulation, elevated cortisol causing hippocampal atrophy, and neuroinflammation. Treating depression with antidepressants and psychotherapy is essential for both mental health and dementia prevention.', '[0,0.09375,-0.28125,-0.4375,0,-0.25,-0.515625,0.484375,-0.0546875,-0.96875,0.28125,0.703125,0.1328125,-0.578125,0.140625,-0.15625,-0.4375,-0.3671875,-0.359375,-0.0078125,0.1796875,0,-0.40625,-0.1171875,0.0625,-0.3671875,-0.1171875,0.59375,-0.0234375,0.609375,-0.515625,0.2734375,0.453125,0.515625,-0.078125,0.390625,0.25,-0.0859375,-0.8046875,0.1484375,-0.140625,0.6328125,0.203125,0.5390625,-0.59375,-0.3203125,0.3203125,-0.28125,0.0390625,-0.3359375,-0.078125,0.140625,-0.34375,-0.0546875,-0.2578125,0.0390625,0.09375,-0.078125,0.5234375,-0.453125,0.3046875,-0.421875,0.59375,0.53125,-0.125,-0.1171875,0.6171875,-0.828125,0.3359375,-0.328125,-0.5859375,-0.125,0.15625,-0.078125,-0.2890625,0.015625,0.1953125,0.0546875,0.3203125,0.328125,-0.8203125,-0.703125,0.234375,0.921875,-0.0546875,0.1328125,-0.3125,-0.3203125,0.6484375,-0.296875,-0.0078125,-0.6875,0.2734375,-0.34375,-0.0078125,0.484375,-0.1875,-0.4921875,-0.0078125,-0.3515625,-0.0078125,-0.0390625,0.078125,0.546875,0.4765625,-0.0625,-0.03125,0.625,-0.53125,0.203125,-0.609375,-0.515625,0.0859375,0.1640625,0.6171875,0.3984375,0.5390625,0.1015625,-0.203125,-0.734375,-0.296875,-0.0546875,0.046875,0.1171875,-0.59375,-0.6953125,-0.0390625,0.171875,-0.1328125,-0.390625,-0.640625,0.203125,0.4296875,0.1640625,0.0859375,-0.3203125,0.2421875,0.2578125,-0.0859375,0.3125,-0.1640625,0.015625,-0.515625,0.34375,-0.5234375,0.0078125,0.1171875,-0.28125,-0.15625,0.015625,-0.453125,-0.1875,-0.078125,-0.3203125,0.1875,0,-0.0625,-0.1953125,0.171875,-0.109375,0.046875,0.3046875,-0.3125,-0.65625,0.2109375,-0.046875,-0.3671875,0.0156