  ('Traumatic brain injury (TBI) is associated with increased long-term risk of dementia, particularly Alzheimer''s disease and chronic traumatic encephalopathy (CTE). Even mild TBI (concussion) with loss of consciousness doubles dementia risk in long-term follow-up. Multiple mild TBIs (as in contact sports) have a synergistic effect. Helmets and fall prevention are primary prevention strategies.', '[0,0.5,-0.234375,-0.6640625,0,0.2265625,-0.359375,0.453125,0.078125,-0.984375,0.4375,0.7578125,0.171875,-0.5546875,0.015625,0.1640625,-0.34375,-0.4609375,0.1484375,-0.0234375,0.1015625,0.0703125,0.3125,-0.3671875,0.1796875,0.1328125,-0.1171875,0.40625,0.3828125,-0.1875,0.109375,0.203125,-0.203125,0.1875,-0.0859375,0.0703125,0.3125,-0.265625,-0.3984375,0.2265625,-0.8046875,0.5703125,0.6953125,0.2578125,-0.734375,-0.3203125,0.4609375,-0.140625,-0.296875,-0.25,-0.1015625,0.0234375,0.0078125,0.1796875,0.6328125,0.1640625,0.265625,0.1953125,0.5,-0.171875,0.0859375,-0.46875,0.34375,-0.625,-0.28125,0.7734375,0.0390625,-0.6484375,-0.078125,-0.59375,-0.3359375,-0.390625,0.5078125,-0.4296875,0.6484375,0.6015625,0.046875,0.1640625,0.1953125,0.1171875,-0.4140625,-0.25,0.34375,0.890625,0.03125,0.359375,-0.625,-0.375,0.0625,-0.03125,-0.21875,-0.34375,0.046875,-0.4453125,-0.0625,0.71875,0.046875,-0.171875,0.0859375,-0.1171875,0.1015625,-0.3125,-0.0703125,0.28125,0.2265625,-0.40625,0.1328125,0.3046875,-0.4375,0.453125,-0.03125,-0.234375,-0.71875,0.21875,-0.0703125,0.0625,0.2890625,-0.15625,0.2890625,-0.640625,0.0703125,-0.1328125,-0.609375,0.0703125,-0.21875,-0.375,0.109375,0.203125,-0.234375,-0.359375,-0.7578125,0.4296875,0.296875,-0.1640625,0.3203125,-0.1953125,0.1640625,0.3671875,-0.15625,0.0234375,-0.2421875,-0.1953125,-0.5859375,-0.0703125,-0.4765625,-0.4765625,0.3359375,-0.4140625,0.1640625,-0.125,-0.125,0.15625,0.0078125,-0.3203125,-0.109375,0.0390625,0.09375,-0.125,-0.0703125,0.09375,0.1640625,0.359375,-0.1171875,-0.734375,-0.171875,0.1171875,-0.2109375,0.078125,0.0390625,0.2734