  ('There is no safe level of alcohol consumption for cancer risk (WHO 2023 position statement). Alcohol is causally linked to cancers of the mouth, pharynx, larynx, oesophagus, liver, colorectum, and female breast. Even 1 standard drink per day is associated with increased breast cancer risk (10–15% relative risk increase per 10 g alcohol/day). Risk increases linearly with consumption.', '[0,-0.1875,-0.2265625,-0.6796875,0,0.265625,-0.125,0.09375,0.109375,-0.96875,-0.3984375,0.2109375,0.3828125,0.3125,0.6484375,-0.3203125,0.3984375,-0.5078125,-0.53125,-0.0625,-0.125,-0.78125,-0.515625,-0.796875,-0.8046875,0.8984375,-0.0703125,0.6875,0.25,0.1015625,0.1640625,0.1328125,0.1953125,-0.015625,-0.0625,0.2578125,-0.46875,-0.2421875,-0.7734375,-0.0625,0.4375,-0.484375,-0.578125,-0.390625,0.0078125,-0.6875,0.0546875,-0.84375,0.203125,0.4296875,0.6796875,0.109375,-0.46875,-0.0078125,0.7109375,0.0390625,0.5546875,0.1875,-0.578125,-0.7265625,0.140625,0,0.703125,-0.1015625,0.1953125,-0.546875,-0.421875,-0.515625,-0.5234375,0.515625,-0.59375,0.3984375,-0.203125,0.078125,0.65625,0.5546875,0.109375,0.140625,-0.3203125,0.015625,-0.6953125,0.4140625,0.1796875,0.8671875,-0.3671875,-0.203125,-0.609375,-0.1640625,-0.0390625,-0.5234375,-0.140625,0.2734375,0.59375,-0.859375,-0.2265625,-0.140625,0.5234375,0.21875,0.515625,0.0625,-0.1875,-0.109375,-0.5859375,0.0703125,0.1015625,0.0078125,-0.7265625,0.828125,-0.203125,-0.2890625,-0.65625,0.1328125,-0.640625,0.640625,-0.6171875,-0.5546875,0.2265625,0.2578125,-0.140625,-0.796875,-0.0703125,0.234375,-0.015625,-0.453125,0.0078125,-0.4296875,0.0234375,-0.1875,0.5625,-0.0859375,-0.1640625,0.1953125,-0.59375,-0.015625,0.4140625,-0.125,0.234375,0.15625,-0.265625,-0.0390625,-0.3515625,-0.1796875,-0.2109375,0.1796875,0.0546875,-0.5546875,-0.0390625,0.140625,0.0078125,0.09375,-0.15625,0.578125,-0.2421875,0.28125,0.0546875,0.1953125,-0.1484375,0.75,-0.203125,-0.0703125,-0.375,-0.53125,-0.6328125,-0.3125,0.0546875,0.375,0.125,-0.078125,0.4453125,-0.21875