  ('Processed meat (bacon, ham, sausages, hot dogs, and deli meats) is classified as a Group 1 carcinogen by IARC — the highest classification, meaning there is sufficient evidence of cancer causation in humans. Each 50 g serving of processed meat per day increases colorectal cancer risk by approximately 18%. Red unprocessed meat is classified IARC Group 2A (probably carcinogenic). Cancer Council Australia recommends limiting red meat to < 500 g/week and minimising processed meat.', '[0,0.015625,-0.2421875,-0.53125,0,0.2578125,0.03125,0.3671875,0.0234375,-0.875,-0.21875,0.171875,0.1796875,-0.1796875,0.1484375,-0.7109375,0.0390625,-0.2578125,-0.625,0,-0.1015625,0,-0.1171875,-0.421875,-0.484375,-0.078125,-0.0078125,0.46875,0.34375,0.1328125,0.09375,0.1015625,0.484375,-0.1328125,0.0234375,-0.1640625,-0.4921875,-0.1484375,-0.6875,-0.140625,-0.109375,-0.5,-0.1640625,0.15625,0.453125,-0.4921875,0.0390625,0.171875,-0.265625,0.2265625,0.4375,0.046875,0.453125,0.2578125,0.1328125,-0.171875,0.328125,0.1953125,-0.046875,-0.5703125,-0.015625,0.046875,-0.078125,-0.0703125,0.2109375,0.125,-0.3203125,0.0390625,-0.5078125,0.546875,-0.34375,0.421875,0.078125,0.0625,0.7265625,0.21875,0.03125,-0.21875,0.0390625,-0.03125,-0.046875,0.234375,-0.25,0.375,-0.09375,-0.3671875,0.28125,-0.0546875,0.078125,0.265625,0.015625,0.5546875,-0.046875,-0.5625,-0.0390625,0.203125,0.15625,-0.0703125,0.1640625,-0.0078125,-0.015625,0.125,0.5390625,-0.203125,-0.296875,-0.0078125,-0.125,0.0390625,0.171875,-0.3046875,-0.078125,-0.3828125,-0.5625,-0.015625,0.109375,-0.109375,-0.0390625,-0.453125,-0.0859375,-0.65625,-0.1171875,0.4375,0.03125,0.265625,0.03125,-0.1953125,-0.0625,0.125,0.0703125,-0.2265625,0.0703125,0.21875,-0.21875,0.078125,-0.015625,0.0078125,-0.25,0.0625,-0.1875,0.125,-0.015625,0.046875,0.015625,0.3984375,-0.4296875,-0.234375,-0.0078125,0.2578125,-0.1953125,0.109375,-0.03125,0.5859375,-0.1484375,0.34375,-0.1640625,0.2109375,-0.0234375,0.5078125,-0.0234375,-0.015625,0.0703125,-0.1015625,-0.2578