  ('Magnesium (NIH ODS): Recommended dietary intake (RDI) = 310–320 mg/day for adult women; 400–420 mg/day for adult men. Upper tolerable intake level for supplemental magnesium = 350 mg/day. Forms with best bioavailability: magnesium glycinate (amino acid chelate), magnesium malate, magnesium citrate. Magnesium oxide has only 4% bioavailability. Magnesium deficiency is common in type 2 diabetes, hypertension, and alcohol use disorder. Meta-analysis (2016): supplemental magnesium reduces SBP by ~2 mmHg and DBP by ~1.78 mmHg.', '[0,0.8828125,-0.3125,-0.6640625,0,0.3359375,0.5859375,0.578125,0.0078125,-0.875,-0.4453125,0.4453125,-0.140625,0.109375,0.4765625,-0.5546875,-0.109375,-0.0859375,-0.453125,0.0703125,-0.484375,0.1640625,-0.1953125,-0.515625,-0.78125,-0.1171875,-0.3828125,-0.484375,-0.171875,-0.390625,-0.0390625,0.234375,0.296875,-0.0859375,-0.109375,0.3515625,0.3515625,0.0859375,-0.2421875,-0.40625,0.2578125,-0.2734375,-0.3515625,0.359375,-0.125,0.171875,-0.1171875,0.1953125,0.4453125,0.71875,-0.0625,0.2734375,-0.375,0.2890625,-0.328125,0.6484375,0.1953125,0.1171875,-0.6640625,-0.6953125,0.09375,0.09375,0.734375,-0.5078125,0.0390625,-0.5234375,-0.5234375,-0.234375,-0.15625,0.4921875,-0.1875,0.6875,0.171875,-0.2265625,0.40625,0.2578125,-0.2421875,-0.421875,-0.8984375,0.1015625,0.0625,-0.125,0.296875,0.6640625,-0.40625,-0.125,0.375,-0.2109375,0.6484375,0,-0.03125,0.8359375,-0.046875,0.046875,0.03125,0.2109375,-0.234375,0.5625,0.7265625,-0.59375,0.3125,-0.2734375,-0.4375,0.109375,0.8984375,-0.09375,0.7421875,0.234375,-0.015625,0.578125,-0.78125,-0.671875,-0.1015625,-0.1328125,0.703125,0.015625,0.1875,-0.828125,-0.484375,0.2265625,0.453125,0.3125,0.1015625,-0.15625,-0.0078125,0.2890625,0.6875,0.4375,0.2109375,-0.1875,-0.7734375,0.3203125,0.046875,-0.2734375,0.0234375,-0.0859375,0.046875,0.171875,-0.03125,0.0234375,0.0703125,-0.015625,-0.515625,-0.578125,0.3984375,0.4296875,0.1953125,-0.21875,0.421875,0.0625,-0.265625,-0.3046875,-0.265625,-0.09375,-0.3984375,0.2343