  ('Zinc (NIH ODS): RDI 8 mg/day female; 11 mg/day male. Upper tolerable limit 40 mg/day. Zinc deficiency associated with impaired immune function, delayed wound healing, hair loss, reduced testosterone, and loss of taste/smell. Supplemental forms with best bioavailability: zinc picolinate, zinc gluconate, zinc bisglycinate. Excess zinc (> 40 mg/day) can cause copper deficiency (competes for intestinal absorption). Zinc sulfate has lower bioavailability and poorer GI tolerance.', '[0,0.5,-0.1015625,-0.703125,0,0.0703125,0.0546875,0.1796875,0.1484375,-0.84375,-0.5703125,-0.0703125,0.25,0.171875,0.8671875,-0.609375,-0.703125,-0.2734375,-0.28125,0.0234375,-0.3203125,0.6796875,-0.625,-0.4453125,-0.7890625,0.1875,-0.1796875,-0.125,0.09375,0.4375,0.4140625,0.234375,0.1484375,-0.171875,-0.0703125,0.0546875,0.28125,0.0859375,-0.1953125,0.25,0.4609375,-0.1953125,-0.15625,0,0.203125,-0.6015625,-0.0859375,0.1953125,0.53125,0.421875,0.3125,0.6640625,0.2578125,0.2734375,-0.0703125,0.734375,-0.1875,0.1796875,-0.1171875,-0.8671875,0.078125,-0.2890625,0.375,0.015625,0.4453125,-0.125,-0.1953125,0.4453125,-0.328125,-0.03125,-0.40625,0.421875,0.2265625,-0.125,0.453125,0.3046875,-0.1875,-0.0078125,-0.3359375,0.3203125,0.03125,-0.203125,0.5078125,0.4921875,0.4296875,-0.3671875,0.015625,-0.2421875,0.15625,0.0859375,-0.171875,0.9140625,0.28125,-0.09375,0.125,0.0546875,0.265625,0.375,0.3828125,-0.1953125,0.2890625,0.140625,-0.015625,0.078125,0.5625,0.3828125,0.015625,0.3046875,0.0234375,0.375,0.078125,-0.078125,-0.5234375,0.03125,0.6171875,-0.1875,0.2265625,-0.5390625,-0.484375,-0.0703125,-0.1015625,0.359375,-0.25,-0.40625,0.296875,0.203125,0.3671875,0.0703125,0.046875,-0.296875,-0.7265625,0.203125,-0.0234375,-0.3046875,0.3359375,0.03125,-0.0390625,0,0.1328125,-0.1640625,-0.09375,-0.09375,0.0234375,-0.578125,0.296875,0.0703125,0.3125,0.3828125,0.1953125,0.09375,-0.2421875,-0.25,0.1015625,0.21875,-0.4140625,0.0703125,0.265625,0.0390625,0.328125,-0.2734375,0.109375,-0.28125,-0.84375,-0.27343