  ('Curcumin (from turmeric): Bioavailability of curcumin alone is < 1% due to poor absorption, rapid metabolism, and rapid elimination. Co-administration of piperine (5 mg, from black pepper) increases curcumin bioavailability by approximately 20-fold. Recommended dose: 500–1,000 mg curcuminoids/day with piperine. Anti-inflammatory mechanisms: inhibition of NF-κB, COX-2, and prostaglandin E2. Level II evidence for knee OA symptom relief. Mild antiplatelet activity — caution with anticoagulants.', '[0,-0.328125,-0.2890625,-0.6953125,0,-0.1484375,0.2578125,0.5234375,0.171875,-0.9609375,-0.2421875,-0.484375,0.1640625,-0.296875,0.1328125,-0.5,-0.046875,0.1953125,-0.75,0.0703125,-0.359375,-0.3828125,-0.859375,-0.3046875,-0.46875,0.21875,0.0390625,0.265625,0.125,-0.0546875,0.171875,-0.0390625,0.578125,-0.234375,-0.328125,0.7109375,-0.2265625,0.0703125,-0.265625,-0.15625,0.3125,-0.3828125,-0.2109375,0.4375,-0.453125,0.3515625,0.328125,-0.1640625,0.1875,0.3125,-0.1015625,0.2890625,0.1796875,0.3125,-0.0625,0.75,-0.375,-0.203125,-0.2109375,-0.2890625,0.171875,0.0859375,0.0234375,-0.2109375,0.1953125,0.15625,0.578125,0.28125,-0.2421875,0.125,0.046875,-0.1796875,0.375,0.2421875,0.328125,-0.2578125,-0.2265625,-0.1015625,-0.578125,0.6640625,-0.0234375,0.375,0.703125,0.5,-0.1953125,-0.1484375,-0.5390625,-0.125,-0.40625,0.140625,-0.3125,0.703125,0.1328125,0.390625,-0.0546875,-0.09375,0,0.09375,0.0703125,-0.1171875,0.390625,-0.09375,0.125,-0.375,0.5,0.109375,0.2578125,-0.0625,-0.3671875,-0.515625,-0.5703125,0.40625,-0.2890625,-0.1328125,-0.3046875,-0.109375,0.5234375,-0.8203125,-0.53125,-0.546875,-0.046875,-0.21875,-0.0859375,0.6328125,-0.546875,-0.09375,0.2109375,-0.078125,-0.3046875,-0.2734375,0.0078125,0.125,0.359375,-0.453125,0.3671875,-0.2578125,0.140625,-0.171875,-0.0078125,-0.6328125,-0.21875,-0.296875,-0.2265625,-0.5,-0.09375,-0.609375,-0.2265625,-0.34375,0.0625,0.2421875,-0.328125,-0.0703125,0.09375,0.6171875,-0.3359375,0.15625,-0.171875,-0.296875,0.1640625,-0.4453125,0.46