  ('Vitamin K2 (menaquinone-7, MK-7): The Rotterdam Study (2004) found the highest quartile of vitamin K2 intake associated with 57% reduction in cardiovascular mortality and 52% reduction in aortic calcification compared to the lowest quartile. MK-7 (90–180 µg/day) activates osteocalcin (bone matrix protein) and matrix Gla protein (MGP, which inhibits arterial calcification). MK-7 has superior half-life (3 days) vs MK-4 (hours). Caution with warfarin anticoagulation.', '[0,0.0859375,0.015625,-0.234375,0,-0.3828125,0.3359375,0.8671875,0.09375,-0.9453125,-0.1796875,0.296875,-0.1640625,0.3515625,0.5859375,-0.5859375,0.328125,-0.140625,0.25,0.015625,-0.1875,0.2109375,-0.7421875,-0.3515625,-0.703125,-0.25,-0.0859375,-0.4375,0.109375,0.140625,0.109375,-0.0390625,0.5,-0.0625,-0.1484375,0.25,-0.34375,-0.0859375,-0.53125,-0.046875,0.3125,0.0078125,0.15625,0.5078125,-0.28125,0.3515625,0.2109375,-0.4765625,-0.234375,0.1796875,-0.2890625,0.0703125,0.1640625,0.0390625,-0.0703125,0.2421875,0.4921875,-0.03125,-0.40625,-0.359375,-0.1328125,-0.078125,0.0546875,0,0.15625,0.1640625,0.3203125,-0.203125,0.1953125,0.5625,-0.109375,0.5078125,-0.1796875,0.03125,0.109375,-0.1171875,-0.21875,-0.2421875,-0.3984375,0.359375,-0.3828125,0.46875,0.1953125,0.625,-0.046875,-0.390625,0.421875,0.15625,-0.296875,-0.5234375,-0.109375,-0.2734375,0.359375,-0.3671875,0.2890625,-0.359375,0.1328125,-0.3203125,0.1953125,-0.0546875,0.2109375,0.234375,-0.265625,-0.359375,0.1328125,-0.34375,0.515625,-0.5390625,0.1015625,0.2265625,-0.78125,-0.0078125,0.4375,0.0625,0.171875,0.109375,-0.1796875,-0.53125,-0.125,0.0078125,-0.609375,0.03125,-0.296875,-0.0078125,-0.2265625,0.1796875,0.2734375,0.1171875,-0.1640625,-0.2109375,-0.484375,-0.1328125,-0.015625,-0.03125,0.1484375,0.03125,0,0.1328125,0.09375,0.1171875,-0.1953125,-0.0625,-0.296875,0.09375,-0.265625,-0.2578125,-0.1171875,-0.234375,0.1015625,0.109375,0.546875,0.2265625,0.0546875,0.0859375,-0.0859375,-0.234375,-0.234375,0.2578125,0.1171875,-0.2578125,0.1953125,-