  ('Levothyroxine absorption is reduced by concurrent mineral supplementation. Iron reduces thyroxine absorption by 30–40% via chelation in the gastrointestinal tract. Calcium carbonate, magnesium, and zinc have similar chelating effects. Biotin supplementation interferes with TSH immunoassay results (falsely lowers TSH, falsely elevates fT4) — stop biotin ≥ 72 hours before thyroid blood tests. Minimum separation between levothyroxine and mineral supplements: 2 hours.', '[0,0.3515625,0.1171875,-0.453125,0,0.0625,0.4921875,0.3515625,0.1484375,-0.9921875,-0.4921875,0.7109375,0.140625,-0.2109375,0.890625,-0.375,0.2109375,-0.6171875,0.453125,0.046875,-0.3359375,0.1171875,-0.890625,-0.7734375,-0.65625,0.15625,-0.046875,-0.2109375,0.125,-0.1484375,-0.328125,-0.2421875,0.65625,-0.0234375,-0.3046875,0.046875,0.1015625,0.0390625,-0.3515625,0.25,0.40625,-0.390625,-0.3046875,0.171875,-0.28125,-0.3828125,0.5546875,0.34375,-0.09375,0.2734375,-0.3125,-0.140625,0.578125,0.1796875,-0.171875,0.5546875,-0.6015625,0.1953125,-0.421875,-0.65625,-0.1015625,-0.359375,0.0078125,-0.1328125,0.1171875,0.390625,-0.0625,0.8828125,-0.671875,-0.140625,-0.0234375,0.296875,-0.25,0.1171875,0.1015625,0.3515625,0.1484375,-0.015625,0.03125,0.09375,-0.4453125,-0.203125,-0.4765625,0.828125,-0.265625,-0.359375,0.3359375,0.0625,0.0859375,-0.28125,-0.140625,0.53125,-0.2578125,0.8125,0.3984375,-0.078125,0.125,0.5390625,0.078125,0.1171875,0.078125,-0.34375,0.0859375,-0.1484375,0.4296875,0.125,-0.375,-0.375,0.2265625,0.7265625,-0.53125,-0.1796875,0.34375,0.265625,0.21875,0.0078125,0.59375,-0.2109375,0.3203125,-0.3828125,-0.0546875,0.3671875,0.4375,0.4453125,0.1484375,-0.0078125,0.2890625,0.4609375,0.4453125,-0.1875,0,-0.2578125,0.75,-0.421875,-0.203125,-0.15625,-0.3203125,0.21875,0.3125,-0.0625,-0.0859375,-0.5078125,-0.1171875,-0.6484375,0.078125,0.0859375,-0.046875,-0.28125,-0.0859375,0.296875,-0.40625,-0.2109375,0.0703125,-0.0859375,-0.328125,-0.21875,0.0078125,-0.1953125,-0.0625,0.3046875,0.484375,0.03125,-